    if (currentMode != desiredMode) {
        //we only need to handle this case. If desired == current, the flow stops (no msg returned)
        //also means, no unneccessary SB API calls
        return msg;
    }

}

/*  Found out that the battery retains the last command in manual/API command. Could be a bug or a feature.
    However, since the previous command was almost certainly 

    "/api/v2/setpoint/charge/" + sonnen_watts;

    We have to make sure it is set to 0, since we don't want to charge
    Also, just to be on the safe side, will set the discharge also to 0 - so it is just idling, which is what we want in this case.
    Until some other part of the flow wants it to charge or discharge (the latter simply by giving back control via 
    OperatingMode = "2").

    */


