/* ok, after having tested this for a couple of days, I can safely say that defining the status of

"is the battery charging" by a combination of
- operatingMode = "1" (battery is is manual/API mode)
- isBatteryCharging

is unreliable, I think mostly because the "BatteryCharging" status from the API is erroneous/unpredictable.
So, instead of relying on 

var operatingMode = msg.payload.OperatingMode;
var isBatteryCharging = msg.payload.BatteryCharging;

I will have to set a status in the global context and flip the switch on that.

*/

var operatingMode = msg.payload.OperatingMode;
var isBatteryCharging = global.get("isBatteryCharging");

if (operatingMode == "1" && isBatteryCharging) {
    //send to second output only, I'm already charging

    return [null, msg];

} else {
    //send to first output only, start charging
    return [msg, null];
}

